systemInfos

private final Map<String,Set<String>> systemInfos
System information of the unit. Internally the system information is stored as property link and could be evaluated only after complete dimension parsing. The key of the map is the system name, the values are the related names of the units.

See Also:
Dimension_mxJPO.prepare(ParameterCache_mxJPO)

settings

private final Map<String,String> settings
Holds all unit specific settings for a dimension. The settings are stored internally as property. Therefore the settings could be extracted only after a complete parsing.

properties

private final Set<AdminProperty_mxJPO> properties
Holds all unit specific properties for a single unit. The properties includes settings and the link to the system property. While the dimension is parsed the properties holds also the settings, and systemInfos.

Method Detail

compareTo

public int compareTo(Dimension_mxJPO.Unit _toCompare)
Compares this dimension with _toCompare dimension. The algorithm checks name for both dimension and is defined as:
  • If both name are null then a "0" is returned.
  • If only the name of this unit is null then a "-1" is returned.
  • If only the name of the _toCompare unit is null then a "1" is returned.
  • Otherwise the value of a string compare between both names is returned.

Specified by:
compareTo in interface Comparable<Dimension_mxJPO.Unit>
Parameters:
_toCompare - unit instance to which this unit must be compared to
Returns:
"0" if both units are equal; "1" if greater; otherwise "-1"

appendDelta

protected void appendDelta(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                           Dimension_mxJPO.Unit _current,
                           StringBuilder _cmd,
                           StringBuilder _postCmd)
                    throws UpdateException_mxJPO

Appends the MQL delta commands to updated current unit definition _current to this new target unit definition.

FYI: For each setting which is modified a modify unit must be defined as prefix or otherwise only the last setting is correct (issue in MX kernel).

Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_current - current unit definition in MX (or null if currently not existing)
_cmd - string builder used to append MQL commands
_postCmd - string builder used to append the system information (should be defined at least)
Throws:
UpdateException_mxJPO - if the multiplier or offset is changed

toString

public String toString()
Returns the string representation of this unit. The information includes name, description, label, multiplier, offset, defaultUnit, systemInfos, settings and properties.
